# Product Overview

## What It Does
A PDF document search service. Users upload PDFs, the system extracts text via OCR, embeds it into vectors, and stores them in PostgreSQL+pgvector. Users can then search documents with natural language via web UI, REST API, or CLI chatbot.

## Three Interfaces

### Web UI (`templates/`, `app/main.py`)
- **Search Page** (`/`) — Query box with HTMX, displays matched chunks with document info and scores
- **Chat Page** (`/chat`) — Interactive chat interface with tool calling (replicates CLI chatbot)
- Server-side rendered with Jinja2 templates, single-process architecture

### REST API (`app/routes.py`)
- `POST /api/v1/documents/upload` — Upload and process a single PDF
- `POST /api/v1/documents/query` — Semantic search + LLM-generated answer
- `POST /api/v1/documents/search` — Search-only endpoint (returns chunks, no LLM answer)
- `POST /api/v1/chat` — Chat endpoint with tool calling support
- `GET /api/v1/documents` — List all documents
- Endpoints detect HTMX requests and return HTML fragments when appropriate

### CLI Chatbot (`app/chat.py`)
- Interactive REPL with conversation history
- LLM uses OpenAI tool calling to decide when to search
- Two tools: `search(query)` across all docs, `search_in_book(book_name, query)` for a specific doc
- System prompt includes the full document list with page counts

## Data Flow
1. PDF uploaded → pdf2image → page images (cached)
2. Page images → pytesseract OCR → text per page (cached)
3. Text → sentence splitting → 5-sentence chunks with 1-sentence overlap
4. Chunks → OpenAI embedding → stored in pgvector
5. Query → embed → cosine distance search → top-K chunks → LLM answer

## Batch Ingestion (`app/ingest.py`)
- `make ingest` processes all PDFs in `example-pdfs/`
- Tracks processing status per document: `waiting` → `started` → `finished` / `errored`
- Skips already-finished documents on re-run
- Retries errored documents, reusing cached images/OCR

## Project Structure
```
app/
├── main.py            # FastAPI app, lifespan, template routes (/ and /chat)
├── config.py          # pydantic-settings
├── database.py        # async SQLAlchemy engine, init_db
├── models.py          # Document, Chunk (SQLAlchemy)
├── schemas.py         # Pydantic request/response models
├── routes.py          # API endpoints (handles HTMX requests for HTML fragments)
├── pdf_processing.py  # pdf2image, OCR, chunking
├── embeddings.py      # OpenAI embeddings + LLM
├── cache.py           # Disk cache for images/OCR
├── ingest.py          # Batch PDF ingestion CLI
└── chat.py            # Interactive chatbot CLI
templates/
├── base.html          # Base template with navigation
├── search.html        # Search page template
├── chat.html          # Chat page template
└── search_results.html # Search results fragment (for HTMX)
static/
└── style.css          # Global stylesheet
```
